Vol / Page:  14
Edition:
Quote:  One of the early infamous nineteenth-century Southland illegal stills was run by Owen McShane, who converted the sugary pulp of cabbage tree roots (ti kouka) into a concoction similar to brandy or rum... Missionary and Maori alike made beer from ti kouka.
